abstractText: To determine abundance and composition of the zooplankton community within a waterbody, such as Lake Wenatchee, Washington. Zooplankton are the primary food source for juvenile fish, and Lake Wenatchee is a nursey lake for Sockeye Salmon. Therefore, it is important to monitor zooplankton density and biomass to aid in quantifying food web dynamics.
title: Zooplankton Collection and Identification v1.0
